<% content_for :meta_title, "Discogs Wantlist Helper privacy policy" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and share your information when you use the Discogs Wantlist Helper Chrome Extension." %>

<section data-aos="fade"
         data-aos-duration="800"
         class="container flex flex-col p-5 mx-auto lg:mb-14">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold font-heading text-primary-800">
    Discogs Wantlist Helper privacy policy
  </h1>
  <p class="text-primary-800"><strong>Last updated:</strong> November 9, 2025</p>

  <div class="my-5">
    <div class="mb-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        This Privacy Policy explains how the <strong>Discogs Wantlist Helper</strong> Chrome Extension
        (“the Extension”) handles user information. We take your privacy seriously and are committed
        to protecting your data.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">2. Data Collection</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        The Extension does <strong>not collect, store, or share</strong> any personal data such as names,
        email addresses, or browsing history.
      </p>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        The Extension only uses:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-primary-800">
        <li>• <code>chrome.storage.local</code> to locally save user preferences and data;</li>
        <li>• <code>chrome.storage.identity</code> to initiate a login with Discogs;</li>
        <li>• requests to the <strong>Discogs API</strong> (<%= link_to 'https://api.discogs.com/', 'https://api.discogs.com/', target: '_blank',class: 'underline text-primary-800 underline-offset-4 decoration-dotted decoration-primary-800' %>) to retrieve release or artist information.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>No information from these operations is transmitted to any third-party server other than Discogs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">3. Permissions Used</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">The Extension only requests the permissions strictly necessary for it to function:</p>
      <ul class="text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Chrome storage API</strong> to locally save user preferences and data;</li>
        <li>• <strong>Chrome identity API</strong> to initiate a login with Discogs;</li>
        <li>• <%= link_to 'https://api.discogs.com/', 'https://api.discogs.com/', target: '_blank', class: 'underline text-primary-800 underline-offset-4 decoration-dotted decoration-primary-800' %> to fetch information from the Discogs public API.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">4. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        The Extension does not share any user data with third parties.
        Use of the Discogs API is subject to the <%= link_to 'Discogs Privacy Policy', 'https://support.discogs.com/hc/en-us/articles/360009334513-Privacy-Policy', target: '_blank', class: 'underline text-primary-800 underline-offset-4 decoration-dotted decoration-primary-800' %>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">5. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        The Extension does not set cookies or perform any analytics or tracking of user activity.
      </p>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        The Extension communicates with the Discogs API through a secure HTTPS connection to our server.
        OAuth tokens are transmitted in order to authenticate user actions but are not stored, logged, or shared with any third party.
        Tokens are used only during the active session to perform user-authorized API requests.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">6. External Links</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        The Extension includes a link to
        <%= link_to 'buymeacoffee.com/jeanguillet', 'https://buymeacoffee.com/jeanguillet', target: '_blank', class: 'underline text-primary-800 underline-offset-4 decoration-dotted decoration-primary-800' %>
        to allow users to support the project. This link is purely optional and not a paywall to unlock any feature.
        This link opens in a new browser tab and does not transmit any user data whatsoever.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">7. Data Security</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        All data managed by the Extension is stored locally on your device.
        No data is sent to any private or third-party servers.
        You can remove all stored data at any time by uninstalling the Extension
        or clearing your browser’s local storage.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="my-3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        This policy may be updated to reflect technical or legal changes.
        The most recent version and update date will always be displayed at the top of this document.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="my -3">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-primary-400 font-heading">9. Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-800">
        For any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
        <%= link_to ABOUT['email'],
              "mailto:#{ABOUT['email']}",
              class: 'underline text-primary-800 underline-offset-4 decoration-dotted decoration-primary-800' %>
      </p>
  </div>
